stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Jackie
[Gender] Female
[Combat Experience] None
[Place of Birth] Columbia
[Date of Birth] September 15
[Race] Perro
[Height] 157cm
[Infection Status]
Originium crystals are present on the body's surface, confirmed Infected by medical examination.

[Physical Strength] Excellent
[Mobility] Standard
[Physical Resilience] Standard
[Tactical Acumen] Normal
[Combat Skill] Normal
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Standard

A former Columbian auxiliary police officer who came to Rhodes Island to receive treatment after contracting Oripathy. 
With her father's consent, she joined Rhodes Island as an operator, displaying above average talent in close combat and participating in various missions.

Imaging tests have shown the outlines of her internal organs to be indistinct due to abnormal shadows. Originium granules have been detected in her circulatory system, confirming her to be infected with Oripathy. 

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 3%
Due to short infection duration, only small traces of infection are visible on the surface of the body. 

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.16u/L
Thanks to timely treatment and physical fitness, the current prognosis is optimistic. With regular treatment, there will not be much burden on the body.

An energetic Perro girl. 
She is always full of vigor and never remains down for long. As she acts friendly to everyone, she is well-liked by most operators and some older operators even treat her as a cherished sister or daughter. 
She enjoys regaling others with stories of her father's glorious deeds.

As everyone knows, most Infected are able to cast Arts without the help of an Arts Unit. 
On one hand, this is equivalent to using the Originium within one's body for casting Arts, which is likely to exacerbate one's Oripathy. On the other hand, mildly infected individuals like Jackie aren't able to channel much energy for Arts. 
For this reason, even Infected Casters often prefer to cast Arts through an Arts Unit whenever possible. Similarly, Rhodes Island provides an Arts Unit to every Caster operator. 
——In fact, the Engineering Department is very passionate about designing Arts Units of all shapes and sizes. One of their favorite pastimes is developing 'Arts Units' that look nothing like conventional units— and often don't work at all. 
The Arts Unit that hangs at Jackie's waist, gun-type Arts Unit PT-29, is the pride of the Engineering Department. 
Regrettably, even though Jackie applied for such an Arts Unit, it is only due to a habit formed while serving as an auxiliary police officer. Jackie herself is incredibly uninterested in the subject of Arts and her scores are very disappointing. Because of this, this Arts Unit is mostly an accessory to this day.

According to Jackie, her mother passed away from complications during her birth and she was single-handedly raised by her father. Jackie greatly reveres her father. 
She will happily describe in great detail how amazing of a policeman her father is, how many people he's helped and what accolades he's received. Some of her teammates can even recite her entire speech from beginning to end by heart now. 
Her story may be hyperbolic to some extent, but her father was still willing to bring his own infected daughter to Rhodes Island in person. Throughout his short stay in Rhodes Island, he never openly displayed any animosity towards the other Infected, and even remained agreeable to his daughter joining Rhodes Island after learning about some of Rhodes Island's more dubious activities. At the very least, he is not overly biased towards the Infected, even if he is just exercising self-restraint. That alone is already very rare amongst the non-Infected. 
Jackie's good manners and lively attitude in daily life is likely also a result of her father's teachings. 
From that perspective, her father is indeed a policeman worth respecting, and a good father.

Some people hold on to their hatred of the Infected even when they've become Infected themselves. Contrarily, some never hold much enmity towards the Infected, even while they're still uninfected. 
Jackie is one of those people. 
Perhaps as a result of her father's teachings, Jackie has never treated the Infected with hostility, unlike most other people. After overcoming her initial horror, she was able to quickly come to terms with her new identity as an Infected. 
It is possible that since she was showered in love from a young age, Jackie has a great capacity for love towards others——This can be considered a legitimate ability, as rare as it is. After coming to Rhodes Island, not only did this ability allow her to befriend others easily, it also gave her a new goal——To help the other Infected. 
Besides curing her Oripathy, she also wants to lend a hand to the other Infected. To her, it is only natural to do so.

The things we encounter and the people we meet often leave me with a sense of foreboding, afraid that our efforts towards a brighter future are all for naught. 
However, whenever I see a youngster like Jackie brimming with purity, kindness and vigor, I am reminded of my conviction: To guide these youngsters along the path of learning, so that they may gain more knowledge of the world, and help make it a better place. 
——Instructor Guericke's remarks towards Jackie in her Intermediate General Studies class

skins.description:
An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.

<color name=#ffffff>0011 Tempest Series New Release/Take a Leap. Green jacket over a simple shirt, with a pair of jeans and protective pads. Very easy to move in, making it well-suited for the outdoors.</color>

modules.desc:
Operator Jackie has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude for asserting the advantage in close-quarters combat.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Guard Operator during field operations to exercise Fighter responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

Earlier this week, law enforcement officials announced that the major kidnapping case that occurred earlier this weekend in Fussen Furnitureville has been cracked. All suspects are now in custody, and all hostages have been rescued and are currently receiving hospital treatment. Based on facts previously made available by the police, the syndicate responsible has been active in this state as well as our three neighbors, with a focus on hijacking and kidnapping. Seventeen cases this year alone have been linked to them, all striking panic in the populace. Working across state lines to follow developments in the case, Homeland Security employed disciplined units under a single chain of command to finally put this malicious gang behind bars. Justice has finally been served, and the citizens' lives and property safe once again.
However, this week some have continued raising doubts about the police announcement, claiming that credit for the breakthrough goes to a young officer from the auxiliary forces, who is presently unnamed but has captured public attention in recent days. Following the end of the case, footage from a number of mall cameras has circulated on the intercity net. They show a young Perro female in a city police uniform but without a badge hopping onto the furniture store's roof from a nearby building, marking the start of a one woman chase—and eventually brawl—with the gangsters, lasting a whole forty minutes, and ending with her pacifying them all before law enforcement arrived bizarrely late to the scene. The young woman in the video is exceptionally athletic, making use of furniture from every room of the house to contend with the gangsters, skillfully enough to leave many wide-eyed. In the most viral clip, eight of them have her surrounded with edged and bolt-loaded weapons, then in the blink of an eye she grabs a mysterious weapon—said by the store's owner to be no more than a steel chair whose unique design struggled to sell—after which she subdues all the gangsters in short order. The public will not be forgetting her heroism any time soon.
In response to these inquiries, law enforcement official have stated that despite her nonstandard uniform, the woman in footage was in fact a special agent they dispatched to the precinct to secretly tail the gang, with orders to take action from within and subdue the criminals. The idea that the footage shows a 'vigilante' or 'police nonfeasance' is categorically false, and rumors that their department and the criminals were 'in cahoots' are not only utterly baseless, but 'harmful to police image.'
In contrast, eyewitnesses report that after singlehandedly taking down over a dozen gangsters and freeing the hostages, the mysterious young woman was promptly arrested and taken away by police. Some have even identified her as possibly the valorous officer who rescued a number of people during a major Originium safety accident last year, and exposed the former mayor's misdeeds. Law enforcement officials have yet to comment on this. We have made a request for this 'special agent' to come to our station for an interview, which the police have refused, citing her current hospitalization.

voice_lines.voiceText: Doctor, let me help!
Doctor, you've been sitting there for a while, that's really unhealthy. Come do some stretches with me! Exercise and recover your energy. That way, you'll be able to work better.

Doctor, Doctor! She's here at Rhodes Island! Ah, her codename should be Dur-nar now. Anyway, she's really amazing! I've only ever seen her in recruitment ads before! She's also a really good person! She gave me so many snacks, ehehe.
Doctor, I'm actually pretty lithe for my age, you know. Let me show you a standing backflip! Watch!
This gun? Oh, it's a gun-type Arts... Arts something. Ah, right, Arts Unit! I applied for one out of habit when I came here, but I still prefer my fists over Arts.
Even though I know I'm very lucky, I only realized how badly other Infected are doing after coming to Rhodes Island... Doctor, what can I do to help? I really want to help them!
...Hm? Ah, Doctor! I'm writing a letter to my dad. Eh, I haven't introduced my dad to you yet? He's a really amazing policeman, you know! Let me tell you how great he is!

Actually, it was my dad who suggested Rhodes Island. After he found out you could treat Oripathy, he pushed really hard for me to be able to come here. I don't really want to be away from him, but I know that he'll be happiest if I live a healthy life.

You're really reliable, although dad is still better. Yup, you're now the second most reliable person in my heart! Hehe. Ah, Doctor, I talked a lot about you in my letters to dad. He said he really wants to meet you!
Doc——! Ah, Doctor's asleep. I'll have to be quieter...
Nice to meet you, Doctor! I'm the new operator, codename Jackie! I used to be an auxiliary police officer in Columbia. Let's get along!
Amazing... It feels even more amazing than dad...
Eh, am I being promoted? Wow, that's great!
I've learnt a lot living at Rhodes Island... Maybe I can even catch up to dad one day! Doctor, I'll continue to work hard. Please guide me well~
I'm here!
I'll work hard!
Let's do our best!
Mission start!
Doctor, is it my turn?
Warming up complete!
Leave it to me!
Time for me to show my power!
Grit Those Teeth!
You shall not pass!
Don't look down on me!
I'll do it in one go!
I thought we were gonna lose a few time, but we actually won in the end. Doctor, you're amazing!
Doctor, Doctor, I've worked hard!
Doctor, want me to chase after them?
Sorry, Doctor. If only I'd put in more effort...
It's so big inside!
Ahhhh!
Hi, Doctor~
Arknights.

Doctor, Happy New Year! This New Year, I'll be celebrating right here at Rhodes Island. Hehe, I've already written to dad, explaining how I'm learning to stand on my own, and how Rhodes Island is a place he can trust. Um, I do feel a bit lonely sometimes. But celebrating with my fellow operators makes up for it!
Ah, it's Doctor!

Doctor! Happy birthday! My dad always taught me birthdays are best spent doing something kind for others. So I'm thinking, how about we head to the kitchen? We can help the logistics operators with today's grocery delivery. Hehehe, who knows? We might just stumble upon some exciting surprises!

'Walk a mile in someone else's shoes before extending a helping hand.' Now I get why the Infected I met before didn't want to accept help or even talk much. I've learned a lot at Rhodes Island. When I return to Columbia, all this will help me become a better police officer.
